Feeling a lump in your breast can be alarming, but not all lumps are cancerous. One common type, especially in women aged 15-35, is a fibroadenoma—a benign, non-cancerous lump. It’s smooth, firm, and moves easily under the skin. While they are often harmless and can shrink on their own, it's essential to consult your doctor for peace of mind. Regular self-exams and staying informed are key! 💪
